# 6. きっと、今からだって

Minori: Kohane!
Minori: Hmm... I don't see her... Where'd she go...?
An: Huff... Huff... Huff...
Minori: Wait, was that An?!
Minori: (It looked like Kohane was looking for An... So, if I chase after her, I might be able to find Kohane at the same time!)
Minori: An! Wait!
Minori: N-No...! She's too fast...!
Minori: Hang on! I think Shiho went that way just now...!
Minori: Hello? Shiho?!
Shiho: <Minori? Did you find her?>
Minori: I haven't found Kohane yet, but An just ran your way!
Shiho: <An? You mean Kohane's friend...?>
Minori: Yeah, her! She has really long hair with lots of stars in it! Also, um...! She's super upbeat and spirited!!
Minori: I'm pretty sure Kohane's been looking for An. So, if we somehow manage to catch her, Kohane should follow soon after!
Minori: So if you see An, could you call out to her?
Shiho: <Okay... Then, I'll try looking for her.>
Shiho: Let's see... Someone with really long hair and lots of stars in it... And a spirited personality...
Shiho: Wait, what did she mean by “spirited”...?
An: Huff huff... I'm exhausted...! My legs feel like they're gonna explode!
Shiho: (Huh...?! Isn't that her?)
Shiho: (Also, has she been running this entire time after bolting from our classroom? She must have a ridiculous amount of stamina...)
Shiho: Excuse me. You're An Shiraishi, right...?
An: Wah?! Y-You scared me... Yes, I am... Wait, you're...
Shiho: My name is Shiho Hinomori. I'm Kohane Azusawa's classmate.
Shiho: Would you mind if we talked for a bit?
Kohane: Hmm... I still can't find An...
Rin: <Sorry, Kohane... I really wish I could help you more...>
Kohane: No, Rin, don't blame yourself. I mean, it's a big festival with lots of people.
Kohane: Still... What am I supposed to do? I can't call An or anything since I'm the one with her phone...
Kohane: (She looked terrified...)
Guest: Uhh... The treasure's supposed to be hiding under those stairs, right?
Guest: Does this mean we have to defeat that wolf to retrieve it?!
Guest: I heard that solving these puzzles was gonna be a challenge, but not a physical one!
Kohane: (Oh no...! Asahina's class is doing that treasure hunt... Is this where everyone's supposed to search?)
Kohane: I-I'm sorry! I'll move out of your way right now...!
Mafuyu: A zombie wolf's head... Azusawa? Is that you?
Kohane: Huh? Y-Yes, but...
Mafuyu: I had a feeling. Thank goodness I found you.
Mafuyu: Shizuku Hinomori told me that there's a girl running around dressed as a wolf and to let her know if I happened to see her. I believe her sister is also looking for you right now...
Kohane: Shiho's looking for me...? Th-Thank you very much for letting me know!
Kohane: Also, I'm sorry for interfering with your activity! Is this where your class is holding its treasure hunt?
Mafuyu: No, that's okay. Our last participants seemed a bit surprised, but they also seemed to enjoy themselves.
Mafuyu: More importantly, your friends must be worried, so please feel free to go.
Kohane: Okay, I'll be going now. Thank you again, Asahina...!
Kohane: If Shiho's out looking for me, then I should probably head back to class for now.
Kohane: Wait, now that I think about it... An might stop by my class again if she still hasn't realized that I'm the one dressed up as the wolf...
Kohane: (But...)
Kohane: ...
Minori: Kohane! Thank goodness I finally found you!
Kohane: Oh, Minori! How did you know I was here?
Minori: I just talked to someone who said that they saw a zombie wolf!
Minori: I asked them for more information and learned that you went this way...
Kohane: I see... I'm sorry for causing you so much trouble, Minori.
Minori: That's totally okay! More importantly! Here's that tool I borrowed from the teachers!
Minori: This should let me get that zipper unstuck, so let's find an empty classroom where we can get this mask off!
Kohane: Okay, thanks...
Minori: There! I got it unstuck, Kohane!
Kohane: Thanks, Minori...
Minori: Is something wrong, Kohane...?
Minori: You don't have to worry about An now since you don't look like a wolf anymore! So, you should go see her...
Kohane: No, it's not that...
Kohane: I wanted her to enjoy the School Festival, but ended up really scaring her...
Kohane: I just wanted everyone to enjoy our haunted house...
Minori: Kohane...
???: I think there's still plenty of time for that...
Kohane: Shiho?! How did you know we were here...?
Shiho: Minori sent me a message. Also, Shiraishi and the others are waiting at our classroom.
Shiho: She even said that she still wants to check out our haunted house.
Kohane: R-Really...?
Shiho: Yeah, also...
Shiho: She said, “I'm sorry for getting scared and running away. We'll be waiting by your class.”
Shiho: A lot did happen and things probably didn't go exactly as planned.
Shiho: But there's still plenty of time to enjoy the School Festival, so you guys should have as much fun as you can.
Kohane: Thanks, Shiho...
Kohane: Actually, I'm wondering if you could do a little favor for me. Would that be okay...?
